Sentencas: Screen-printing technology was developed to fabricate Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte films onto porous NiO-SDC green anode substrates.
Titulo: A screen-printed Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 film solid oxide fuel cell with a Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: After sintering at 1400 degrees C for 4 h, a gas-tight SDC film with a thickness of 12 mu m was obtained.
Titulo: A screen-printed Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 film solid oxide fuel cell with a Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: A novel cathode material of Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta Was subsequently applied onto the sintered SDC electrolyte film also by screen-printing and sintered at 970 degrees C for 3 h to get a single cell.
Titulo: A screen-printed Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 film solid oxide fuel cell with a Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: A fuel cell of Ni-SDC/SDC (12 mu m)/Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta provides the maximum power densities of 1280, 1080, 670, 370, 180 and 73 mW cm(-2) at 650, 600, 555, 505, 455 and 405 degrees C, respectively, using hydrogen as fuel and stationary air as oxidant.
Titulo: A screen-printed Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 film solid oxide fuel cell with a Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: When dry methane was used as fuel, the maximum power densities are 876, 568, 346 and 114 mW cm(-2) at 650, 600, 555 and 505 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: A screen-printed Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 film solid oxide fuel cell with a Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode

Sentencas: ne present fuel cell shows excellent performance at lowered temperatures.
Titulo: A screen-printed Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 film solid oxide fuel cell with a Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-δ cathode
